  change 
8.         
  Final
  exam 




參考教材


1.         
  全球環境變遷導論, 魏國彥、許晃雄, 台灣大學全球變遷研究中心, 1997 (http://140.115.123.30/gis/globalc/index.htm)
2.         
  NASA
  Scientific Visualization Studio (http://svs.gsfc.nasa.gov)




講授方式


　




成績考評


　




備註


　




 





科目名稱


衛星遙測概論




學分數


3




開課學期


九十三學年度第一學期




教學目標


本課程介紹衛星遙測技術之基本原理、特性、限制及應用，以培養學生應用衛星遙測技術解決科學研究上相關問題之能力。本課程重點在於引發學生學習興趣，課堂中將播放若干短片，之後並開放學生討論，鼓勵學生盡量發掘問題並尋找答案，學生每週需完成指定作業並於次週上課時報告所蒐集到的資料。




教學大綱


l         
  基礎篇
1.         
  概論 
2.         
  衛星載具與軌道
3.         
  感測器
4.         
  數位資料
5.         
  地面資料
6.         
  攝影測量原理
7.         
  數位影像處理
8.         
  地理資訊系統
9.         
  光學衛星
l         
  應用篇




參考教材


1.         
  Remote sensing and
  image interpretation, 5th edition, T.M. Lillesand,
  R.W. Kiefer. and J. W. Chipman, John Wiley &
  Sons, 2004 (textbook)
2.         
  Introduction to remote
  sensing, 3rd edition, J.B. Campbell, Taylor
  & Francis, 2002.
3.         
  Physical principles of
  remote sensing, 2nd edition, W.G. Rees, Cambridge University
  Press, 2001.
4.         
  Introductory remote
  sensing - principles and concepts, 1st edition, P.J. Gibson and
  C.H. Power, Routledge, 2000.
5.         
  Introductory remote
  sensing - digital image processing, 1st edition, P.J. Gibson and
  C.H. Power, Routledge, 2000.




講授方式


 課堂講授




成績考評


 平時作業30%，期中考40%，專題報告30%




備註


  




 





科目名稱


物理海洋學




學分數


3




開課學期


九十三學年度第一學期




教學目標


本課程之教學目標在介紹海水之物理性質及海洋中各種物理現象。學生將瞭解這些性質及現象隨時間與空間變化之機制，並進一步學習模擬預測這些變化之方法。




教學大綱


l         
  Introduction
1.         
  A Voyage of Discovery
2.         
  The Historical Setting
3.         
  The Physical Setting
4.         
  Atmospheric Influences
5.         
  The Oceanic Heat Budget
6.         
  Temperature, Salinity, and Density
7.         
  The Equations of Motion
l         
  Midterm Examination 1
8.         
  Equations of
  Motion With Viscosity
9.         
  Response of
  the Upper Ocean to Winds
10.     
  Geostrophic
  Currents
11.     
  Wind Driven
  Ocean Circulation
l         
  Midterm
  Examination 2
12.     
  Vorticity
  in the Ocean
13.     
  Deep
  Circulation in the Ocean
14.     
  Equatorial
  Processes
15.     
  Numerical
  Models
16.     
  Ocean waves
17.     
  Coastal
  Processes and Tides
l         
  Final
  Examination




參考教材


1.         
  Introduction to Physical
  Oceanography, Robert Stewart, Texas
A&M University,
  Fall 2002 revisions (textbook). (http://oceanworld.tamu.edu/home/course_book.htm)
2.         
  Essentials of
  oceanography, Tom Garrison, Thomson, 3rd edition, 352 pp. 2004.
3.         
  Descriptive Physical Oceanography, Pickard, G. L.
  and Emery, W. J., Butterworth-Heinemann, 320 pp. 1990.
4.         
  Ocean Circulation,
  Angela Colling (Editor), 
  Butterworth-Heinemann, 2nd edition, 286 pp. 2001.
5.         
  Waves, Tides and
  Shallow-Water Processes, Wright, J., Colling, A.
  and Park, D. (Editors), Butterworth-Heinemann, 2nd edition, 227 pp. 2000.




講授方式


　




成績考評


平時作業20%，期中考40%，期末考40%




備註


Student's
  grade on line




 





科目名稱


地球科學應用程式設計




學分數


3




開課學期


九十三學年度第一學期




教學目標


This course is set to
  introduce students the commonly used programming languages in earth sciences,
  C++ (C is essentially an older subset of C++) and visual C++. Students will
  develop the ability to write a window-based program to utilize the computer
  resource to solve the mathematical problems in Earth Sciences. Students are
  expected to design and implement a practical project using
  techniques/knowledge learned from this course. The on-site test will be held
  every week to ensure the students are making the appropriate progress.




教學大綱


1.         
  Introduction
2.         
  Getting started
3.         
  The parts of a C++ program
4.         
  Variables and constants
5.         
  Expressions and statements
6.         
  Functions
7.         
  Basic classes
8.         
  More program flow
9.         
  Pointers
10.     
  References
11.     
  Arrays
l         
  Midterm exam
12.     
  Frame
  and resources
13.     
  Window
  message
14.     
  Menu
15.     
  Doc/View
16.     
  Dialog
17.     
  Plotting
  and Printing
18.     
  Redraw
19.     
  Multiple
  document window application
l         
  Final
  exam
l         
  Term
  Project




參考教材


1.         
  Teach yourself C++ in
  21 days, Jesse Liberty, SAMS (http://lib.daemon.am/Books/C++/htm/fm.htm)
2.         
  精通Visual C++ .NET 視窗程式設計, 位元文化, 文魁圖書, 2002




講授方式


　




成績考評


隨堂測驗30%，期中考20%，期末考20%，期末計畫30%




備註


Student's
  grade on line




 




科目名稱


海洋水色衛星遙測




學分數


3




開課學期


九十三學年度第二學期




教學目標


本課程介紹海洋水色衛星遙測方法與理論基礎，主要目標包括：
1.         
  介紹與遙測技術相關之水光學物理觀念
2.         
  概述於水中測量有機與無機物濃度之方法
3.         
  解釋控制水體與輻射能量交互作用現象之數學方程式
4.         
  討論生光模式之發展，並藉以將遙測技術擴展至光學性質複雜之水體
5.         
  推導與評估自然水體之固有光學性質、水質、水色、體反射光譜與遙測間關係




先修課程


普通物理學、微積分、工程數學、衛星遙測概論




教學大綱


1.         
  Introduction
2.         
  Introductory
  Theory
3.         
  The
  Propagation of Atmospheric Photon Fluxes into Natural Waters
4.         
  Composition
  of Natural Waters
5.         
  The
  Impact of Chlorophyll, Suspended Minerals, and Dissolved Organic Carbon on
  Volume Reflectance
6.         
  Chromaticity
  and the Colour of Natural Waters
7.         
  Observations
  of Optical Properties of Natural Waters (The Laurentian
Great Lakes)
8.         
  Remote
  Sensing Over Natural Water
9.         
  Primary
  Production in Natural Water
10.     
  Aquatic
  Remote Sensing in Regional and Global Environmental Monitoring




參考教材


1.         
  Optical
  Properties and Remote Sensing of Inland and Coastal Waters, R. P. Bukata, John H. Jerome, Kirill Ya. Kondratyev and Dimitry V. Pozdnyakov, CRC
  Press, 1995. (textbook)
2.         
  IOCCG
  Educational material on ocean-color (http://www.ioccg.org/education/education.html)
3.         
  Light
  and water, C.D. Mobley, Academic Press, 1994 
4.         
  Light
  and photosynthesis in aquatic ecosystems, J.T.O. Kirk, Cambridge University
  Press, 1994 
5.         
  Ocean
  colour: theory and applications in a decade of CZCS
  experience, Kluwer Academic, 1993 
6.         
  Satellite
  oceanography, 2nd edition, I.S. Robinson, John Wiley & Sons, 1994 




講授方式


 課堂講授+討論




成績考評


 作業60%，論文選讀與報告40%




備註


 




 




科目名稱


遙測影像分析與應用




學分數


3




開課學期


九十三學年度第二學期




教學目標


This course is set to
  introduce students the fundamental concepts of Analysis and applications of
  remote sensing imagery. Students are expected to learn techniques of
  enhancement and quantification of digital imagery acquired by remote sensing.
  Students are also expected to become familiar with processing and analyzing
  data gathered by airborne as well as satellite sensors. The students will be
  able to design and implement a practical digital image processing project
  using techniques learned in class.




教學大綱


1.         
  Introduction
2.         
  Reading data
3.         
  Image restoration
4.         
  Image rectification
5.         
  Image enhancement
6.         
  Image classification
7.         
  Data merging
8.         
  Hyperspectral image analysis




參考教材


1.         
  Remote sensing and
  image interpretation, 5th edition, T.M. Lillesand,
  R.W. Kiefer and J.W. Chipman. John Wiley &
  Sons, 2004 (textbook)
2.         
  ENVI Tutorials, 2003
  edition, Research System Inc, 2003. (textbook)
3.         
  Remote sensing,
  models, and methods for image processing, Robert A. Schowengerdt,
  second edition, San Diego,
  Academic Press, 1997.
4.         
  Introductory Digital
  Image Processing: A Remote Sensing Perspective, John R. Jensen, second
  edition, Prentice Hall, 1995.




